  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening CSO and Citizen Engagement in Zimbabwe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project activities are centred on 
-supporting women and men in artisanal mining to get better organised and achieve registration 
-Project will also promote environmentally friendly practices by mining companies as well as artisanal ( small scale miners)
-The project will engage at national level in influencing the mining law to recognise the needs and rights of communities affected by mining and to increase transparency over the revenue generated by mining companies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will bring about the following change:-
- increased  legal recognition of small scale miners through increased compliance with safety and environmental standards
- Increased environmental protection due to increased capacity of women and men affected by mining to articulate their needs and monitor mining companies
-A responsive mining law that increases environmental protection and transparency over revenues generated</narrative>
  </description>
